article.headline: Colorado St. 91, San Francisco 75
article.story: FORT COLLINS, Colo. -- Travis Franklin scored 10 of his career-high 24 points in the second overtime to lead Colorado State to an 89-75 victory over San Francisco on Sunday. Franklin also kept the game alive at the end of the first overtime with two free throws, tying the score at 73. Dorian Green added 17 points for the Rams (4-2). Dior Lowhorn led the Dons (2-4) with 22 points. Rashad Green had 21. Dorian Green hit a 3-pointer and Franklin had a conventional three-point play and a tip-in basket on Colorado State's first three possessions of the second overtime to pull the Rams ahead 81-73. The lead was 89-73 before San Francisco scored its first points of the second extra period. The Dons missed five shots in the second overtime and didn't score until 40 seconds remained.
